  "osmoses": {
    "synonyms": {
      "fr": "de",
      "0.35521236": 0.2857143
    },
    "usage": {
      "noun": [
        {
          "meaning": [
            "a process by which molecules of a solvent tend to pass through a semipermeable membrane from a less concentrated solution into a more concentrated one, thus equalizing the concentrations on each side of the membrane.",
            "If a solution and solvent or two solutions of different strength are separated by a semi permeable membrane, osmosis can occur."
          ],
          "example": [
            "the process of gradual or unconscious assimilation of ideas, knowledge, etc..",
            "what she knows of the blue-blood set she learned not through birthright, not even through wealth, but through osmosis"
          ]
        }

          "overrating",

          "overvaluation",

          "overvalue"

    },

      "noun": [
        {
          "meaning": "an excessively high estimate.",
          "example": "Such effects would include: overestimates or underestimates of results during the observation and recording phase of an experiment, errors in interpreting the data, and the fabrication of data."
        }
      ],

        {
          "meaning": "estimate (something) to be better, larger, or more important than it really is.",
          "example": "his influence cannot be overestimated"
        }
      ]
